news_header: SEI Investments reported a revenue increase of 14.9% to $557.19 million for Q4 2024, with EPS at $1.19.
news_text: For the quarter ending December 2024, SEI Investments (SEIC) achieved a revenue of $557.19 million, marking a 14.9% increase from the previous year. The earnings per share (EPS) stood at $1.19, up from $0.91 year-over-year. The revenue exceeded the Zacks Consensus Estimate by 0.59%, while the EPS fell short of the estimate of $1.20 by 0.83%. Analysts emphasize the importance of key financial metrics in assessing a company's performance, and SEI's results are part of a broader analysis of stocks recommended by Zacks Investment Research.
